State appears by ADA Kyle Mayo.

Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights filed.
COURT advises defendant of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & questions defendant to understanding.

State moves to DELETE Second and Subsequent Offense and Repeater enhancer on Count 1; COURT GRANTS.

PLEA to Count 1 (Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine <=$3g/PTAC)>>NO CONTEST. 

COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & voluntary made, defendant is competent to represent self and a factual basis & defendant guilty.

COURT ORDERS: WI State Prison (19 months IC, 4 years ES) concurrent to any sentence currently serving. 

CONDITIONS: Assessments/Treatment/Counseling deemed appropriate by agent.  AODA and follow up.  Maintain FTW/School or combination of the two.  Maintain absolute sobriety from and no possession of controlled substances unless valid prescription and taken only as prescribed.  Court costs including DNA sample/surcharge.  Defendant is eligible for CIP/SAP.
